 {"id":"frankenpandas-m3e8","title":"[REALITY-CHECK MEDIUM] SQL parity claim covers only SQLite; pandas read_sql supports PostgreSQL/MySQL/SQLAlchemy","description":"README IO table claims 7 IO formats including SQL mapped to fp_io::read_sql / write_sql with detail SqlIfExists Fail/Replace/Append, transaction-wrapped. Connection type column says SQLite. Reality: pandas read_sql/to_sql works with ANY SQLAlchemy-compatible engine — PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaDB, MS SQL, Oracle. Our impl hardcodes rusqlite::Connection. No DBAPI2 trait abstraction; no PostgreSQL/MySQL backends; no chunksize streaming; params bound parameters filed as frankenpandas-tk3k but unimplemented; coerce_float absent. Suggested: file SQL backend abstraction epic (pub trait SqlConnection) plus PostgreSQL+MySQL feature-gated backends. Or revise README IO row to SQL: SQLite-only via rusqlite so parity claim is not overstated.","notes":"cc-pandas triage 2026-04-22 (commit 3c5c405): capability table cell for '7 IO formats' now reads 'Yes (SQL: SQLite-only via rusqlite; PostgreSQL/MySQL planned)' on the FrankenPandas side and 'Yes (SQL: any SQLAlchemy engine)' on the pandas side, making the comparison honest. New Limitations row names the specific gaps (no SqlConnection trait; no PG/MySQL/MSSQL/Oracle backends; no chunksize streaming; coerce_float absent) and points at the epic. Existing IO detail table at README.md:147 already had 'SQLite' under Connection so no change there. Follow-up epic filed as br-frankenpandas-fd90 (7-slice umbrella: SqlConnection trait, Cargo-feature backend gating, signature lift from rusqlite::Connection, param binding that closes tk3k, chunksize streaming, coerce_float, per-backend live-oracle conformance).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-pandas","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:23:39.633935849Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T12:03:27.811449507Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T12:03:27.808851511Z","closed_by_session":"cc-pandas-m3e8","sour