+{"id":"frankenpandas-m3zib","title":"fd90.125: Recipes example uses write_jsonl + Path::new but neither in prelude (follow-on to fd90.121)","description":"fd90.74-124 README audit. Financial Data Pipeline recipe at lines 1303-1329 imports 'use frankenpandas::prelude::*;' then calls:
  write_jsonl(&vwap, Path::new("daily_vwap.jsonl"))?;

Two compile errors:

1. crates/frankenpandas/src/lib.rs prelude (after fd90.121 expansion) re-exports write_jsonl_string but NOT the path-writing write_jsonl. Verified at crates/fp-io/src/lib.rs:2040 — pub fn write_jsonl(frame, path: &Path).

2. Path::new requires 'use std::path::Path;' — the prelude doesn't re-export std::path::Path (and shouldn't; that's outside frankenpandas's surface).

A user copy-pasting hits:
  error[E0425]: cannot find function 'write_jsonl' in this scope
  error[E0433]: failed to resolve: use of undeclared type 'Path'

Fix:
- Add 'use std::path::Path;' below the prelude import in the Recipes block.
- Expand prelude with the path-based writers used in README documented Recipes: write_jsonl (the file variant). Could also add write_csv, write_json, write_feather, write_parquet for symmetry, since they're already pub-used at the top level (lib.rs:132-144) and users will reasonably expect them after fd90.121's similar expansion of the bytes/string writers.

Scope: prelude expansion (5 path writers) + 1-line README import. Verify with cargo build -p frankenpandas + cargo test -p frankenpandas --lib. Both code change AND README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T11:41:55.997236579Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T11:43:47.530415939Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T11:43:47.527578384Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
